        <briefdescription>
<para>Initializes PL eFUSE with input data given. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>- Input data to be written to PL eFUSE</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><verbatim>  - XST_FAILURE - In case of failure
  - XST_SUCCESS - In case of Success
</verbatim></para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Updates the global variable ErrorCode with error code(if any). </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>Start using the Jtag server to read the JTAG ID and compare with the stored ID, if it not matches return with unique error code. By reading the Jtag ID we will be sure that the JTAG related stuff is working as expected.</para><para>If everything is ok then return PASS.</para>        </inbodydescription>
