      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__xilskey__zynq__ultra__efuse_1gaf56f656aaae5bb0ebc9a3fee806fe202" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>u32</type>
        <definition>u32 XilSKey_EfusePl_Program</definition>
        <argsstring>(XilSKey_EPl *InstancePtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XilSKey_EfusePl_Program</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_xil_s_key___e_pl" kindref="compound">XilSKey_EPl</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Programs PL eFUSE with input data given through InstancePtr. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>- Pointer to PL eFUSE instance which holds the input data to be written to PL eFUSE.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_FAILURE - In case of failure</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS - In case of Success</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>When this API is called: Initializes the timer, XADC/xsysmon and JTAG server subsystems. Returns an error in the following cases, if the reference clock frequency is not in the range or if the PL DAP ID is not identified, if the system is not in a position to write the requested PL eFUSE bits (because the bits are already written or not allowed to write) if the temperature and voltage are not within range. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>Start using the Jtag server to read the JTAG ID and compare with the stored ID, if it not matches return with unique error code. By reading the Jtag ID we will be sure that the JTAG related stuff is working as expected.</para><para>If everything is ok then return PASS.</para>        </inbodydescription>
